Bus crash in Peru Andes kills 18 - report . A bus overturned and plunged down a ravine in the Peruvian Andes , killing at least 18 people and injuring 12 , the state news agency Andina reported on Monday . The agency said the accident happened late on Sunday between the central Andean towns of Hunacayo and Huaychula , and was caused by " the excessive speed of the vehicle . . . " Local radio said the bus was carrying two bands on their way to a party . Police and civil defence officials could not immediately give details of the crash . 
